    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_bloom_644633",
        "quote": "Enjoying fiction requires a shift in selfhood. You give up your own identity and try on the identities of other people, adopting their perspectives so as to share their experiences. This allows us to enjoy fictional events that would shock and sadden us in real life.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Bloom",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_bloom_644633"
